definition: (after a verb or adjective) one who (is) .../(after a noun) person involved in .../-er/-ist/(used after a number or 後|后[hou4] or 前[qian2] to refer to sth mentioned previously)/(used after a term, to mark a pause before defining the term)/(old) (used at the end of a command)/(old) this
lit. to borrow chopsticks/to make plans for sb else

sentences.english: They first came to Atlantic Canada to fish and trade with Aboriginal peoples.
sentences.chinese: 他們最先來到“大西洋加拿大“捕魚及與土箸通商。

sentences.english: Aboriginal peoples were the first people to live in Canada.
sentences.chinese: 土箸是最早居住在加拿大的人。

sentences.english: You still presevere the soul in my inner heart.
sentences.chinese: 你依然保管箸我內心的靈魂。

sentences.english: In which parts of Canada did the Aboriginal peoples first live?
sentences.chinese: 土箸最早期在加拿大何處定居？

sentences.english: Purdah first cold Kam open trunk, jade chopsticks slightly wet red cheek.
sentences.chinese: 深閨乍冷鑑開篋，玉箸微微溼紅頰。

sentences.english: Who are the Aboriginal peoples in Canada?
